 its forms of cultural expression. Contributors address a range of cultural productions, including conduct texts, romances and comic writing, estates-management literature, medical writing, household music and drama and manuscript anthologies. Their studies provide a fresh illustration of the late-medieval household's imaginative scope, its extensive internal and external connections and its fundamental centrality to late-medieval cultural production.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aLiterature Studies 2021. 4aMedieval Studies 2020. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Medieval.2bisacsh  aagriculture.  aclass.  aconduct.  agender.  ahousehold objects.  amanuscript anthology.  amaterial culture.  amedicine.  amedieval domestic life.  amultilingual.1 aBurger, Glenn D., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBurger, Glenn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCritten, Rory G., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCritten, Rory, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDutton, Elisabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKendall, Elliot, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKuipers, Nadine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeahy, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRadulescu, Raluca, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSeaman, Myra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStanbury, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packagez978311128248040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152614422540uhttps